daily_routine: Wakes at 4 AM to check ice conditions via satellite feeds on a cracked
  tablet powered by solar panel. Spends hours studying weather patterns and ice charts,
  looking for stable floes within dog sled range. Maintains his traditional sealskin
  kayak and harpoons that haven't touched seal in three seasons. Teaches his grandson
  Inuit words for ice conditions that no longer exist.
